@startuml
title Viaverse Infrastructure Components — Component Diagram

component "Client Apps\nKMP mobile/web\nNext.js landing/admin" as Apps
component "Edge Layer\nRoute53 / CloudFront / WAF" as Edge
component "Gateway Layer\nAPI Gateway / BFFs\nIngress / ALB" as Gateway
component "Service Layer\nSpring Boot bounded contexts\nHexagonal ports/adapters" as Services
component "Worker Layer\nOutbox relay\nMedia processing\nSchedulers" as Workers
database "Data Layer\nPostgreSQL / Redis / Kafka\nS3 / OpenSearch" as Data
component "Security Layer\nKMS / Secrets Manager\nExternal Secrets\nIAM" as Security
component "Observability Layer\nOTel / Prometheus / Perses\nJaeger / OpenSearch logs" as Obs
component "Delivery Layer\nGitHub Actions\nECR\nIaC / Helm" as CICD
component "Ops Layer\nRunbooks\nAlerts\nBackups / DR" as Ops

Apps --> Edge : HTTPS
Edge --> Gateway
Gateway --> Services : REST/gRPC internal
Services --> Workers : events/jobs
Services --> Data : adapters
Workers --> Data : adapters
Services --> Security : secret/key usage
Services --> Obs : telemetry
Workers --> Obs : telemetry
CICD ..> Gateway : deploy
CICD ..> Services : deploy
Ops --> Obs : alerts/runbooks

note bottom
Infrastructure should support modular monolith-to-microservice evolution.
Services expose stable contracts; infra is replaceable behind adapters/IaC.
end note
@enduml
